DESCRIPTION:Image Credits: Anna Thomas/Hachette India\nJoin author Priya Purushothaman as she discusses her latest book\, The Call of Music\, which traces the layered stories of eight Hindustani musicians keeping classical traditions alive. The session will begin with an introduction by historian Ramachandra Guha\, followed by a guided listening and readings from the book.\n\nLearn more about what went into writing the book. And come away with a deeper understanding of how these individual artists are negotiating caste\, gender\, lineage\, faith and demands of their craft\, in today’s age.
